<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[69475]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA[CaixaForum presents little gems from Madrid's Prado Museum]]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[The exhibition features a selection of 135 small-format works from the Prado Museum, by such artists as El Bosco, Rubens, Goya and Fortuny.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p>CaixaForum is holding an exhibition entitled &quot;La Bellesa Captiva&quot; [Captive Beauty], featuring small-format items that offer visitors a full tour through the history of art, from the Middle Ages to the 19th century, not to mention the Renaissance and Baroque periods and Goya&#8217;s dark paintings.</p>
<p>This is an extremely important exhibition both for its number of loaned items and for the quality of the paintings that have come from the collections at Madrid&#8217;s Prado Museum.</p>
